def periodogram_batch(data, nfft = 2048) :
    ft = np.fft.fftshift(np.fft.fft(data, n=nfft, axis=-1), axes=-1)
    ax = np.linspace(-0.5, 0.5, nfft)
    psds = np.abs(ft)**2 / data.shape[-1]
    return psds, ax

def blackman_tukey(data, nfft = 2048, max_lag : Union[np.ndarray, int] = 100, window_type='bartlett'):
    x = np.asarray(data, dtype=np.float64)
    x = np.expand_dims(x, axis=0) if x.ndim == 1 else x
    B, N = x.shape

    if np.isscalar(max_lag) :
        lens = np.full(B, max_lag, dtype=np.int32)
    else :
        lens = np.asarray(max_lag, dtype=np.int32)
        if lens.shape != (B,) :
            print(lens.shape)
            raise ValueError("max_lag must be a scalar or an array of shape (B,)")
    if np.any(lens <= 0) or np.any(lens > N-1) :
        raise ValueError("max_lag values must be in the range (0, N-1)")
    
    max_lag_val = np.max(lens)
    r_full = np.stack(
        [signal.correlate(row, row, mode='full') for row in x]
    ) / N
    r = r_full[:, N - max_lag_val: N + max_lag_val + 1]

    W = np.zeros((B, 2*max_lag_val + 1), dtype=np.float64)
    for i in range(B) :
        if window_type == 'bartlett' :
            W[i, max_lag_val - lens[i]: max_lag_val + lens[i] + 1] = signal.windows.bartlett(2*lens[i] + 1)
        elif window_type == 'parzen' :
            W[i, max_lag_val - lens[i]:max_lag_val + lens[i] + 1] = signal.windows.parzen(2*lens[i] + 1)
        elif window_type == 'rect' :
            W[i, max_lag_val - lens[i]:max_lag_val + lens[i] + 1] = 1
        else :
            raise ValueError(f"Window type must be - rect, bartlett, parzen. Gotten {window_type}")
    
    r = r * W

    psds = np.fft.fftshift(np.fft.fft(r, nfft, axis=-1), axes=-1)
    psds = np.abs(psds)
    ax = np.linspace(-1/2,1/2,nfft)

    return psds, ax

def welch_periodogram(data, nfft=2048,window_size=64, window_type='rect', overlap_rate=0.5) :
    if window_size <= 0 or window_size > data.shape[-1] :
        raise ValueError("window_size must be in the range (0, len(data)]")
    if window_type == 'rect' :
        window = np.ones(window_size)
    elif window_type == 'hamming' :
        window = signal.windows.hamming(window_size)
    else :
        raise ValueError(f"Window type must be - rect or hamming. Gotten {window_type}")

    ogdim = data.ndim
    if data.ndim == 1:
        data = data[None, :]

    B, N = data.shape

    step = int(window_size * (1 - overlap_rate))
    cnt = (data.shape[-1] - window_size) // step + 1
    psd = np.zeros((B, nfft), dtype=np.float64)
    ax = np.linspace(-0.5, 0.5, nfft)
    for i in range(cnt) :
        segment = data[:, i*step:i*step+window_size] * window
        p, _ = periodogram_batch(segment, nfft)
        psd += p
    psd /= cnt
    return (psd[0] if ogdim == 1 else psd), ax

psd, f = blackman_tukey(data_for_est, max_lag=64, window_type='bartlett')
psd = psd.flatten()
psd_db = 10 * np.log10(psd)
avg_per = 10 * np.log10(periodogram_psd_avg)
alpha = 0.05
win = signal.windows.bartlett(2*64 + 1)
deg = 2 * data.shape[-1] / np.sum(np.square(win))
upper_bnd = deg * psd / chi2.ppf(alpha/2, deg)
lower_bnd = deg * psd / chi2.ppf(1 - alpha/2, deg)
upper_bnd = 10 * np.log10(upper_bnd)
lower_bnd = 10 * np.log10(lower_bnd)


line, = plt.plot(f, psd_db, label="Blackman-Tukey PSD Estimate", zorder=3)
plt.plot(f, avg_per, label="Average Periodogram", color='green', zorder=4, alpha=1, linewidth=0.75)
plt.fill_between(f, lower_bnd, upper_bnd, color=line.get_color(),
    alpha=0.22, label="95% Confidence Interval", zorder=2, edgecolor='none')
plt.title("Blackman-Tukey PSD Estimate with 95% Confidence Interval")
